{"title": "Flight shame over carbon footprint is taking off. Will it come to Asia?", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2024-06-02", "content": "When Ms Hanna Kayhko, a friend of mine, relocated temporarily from her home in Joensuu, Finland, to Oxford, Britain, in 2023, she packed her husband and two children into the family car, a Volvo XC70 sedan, and drove the 3,200km or so over five days.\nFlying would have taken six to eight hours, including a transit in the Finnish capital Helsinki."}